fit-map 0.15.53 — Data validation and management for Engineering Pathway

Usage: fit-map <command> [options]

Commands:
  init                                                        Create ./data/pathway/ with starter standard data
  validate                                                    Run validation (default: JSON schema)
  generate-index                                              Generate _index.yaml files
  export                                                      Render base entities to HTML microdata
  people <validate|push|provision> [file]                     Validate or push people files, or provision auth.users from the roster
  activity <start|stop|status|migrate|transform|verify|seed>  Manage activity stack
  getdx sync                                                  Extract + transform GetDX snapshots
  auth issue                                                  Issue a Supabase-shaped JWT for an existing roster row
  substrate stage                                             Provision a Landmark substrate (init + stack + migrate + seed + provision + self-smoke)
  substrate roster                                            List invariant-satisfying personas from the seeded substrate
  substrate pick                                              Pick one invariant-satisfying persona diversified against recent picks (writes wiki/kata-interview/picks.csv)
  substrate issue                                             Atomically write .env (JWT) and .substrate.json (discovery vector) into a target dir

Options:
  --data=<string>  Path to data directory
  --json           Output as JSON
  --help, -h       Show this help
  --version        Show version

Examples:
  fit-map init
  fit-map validate
  fit-map validate --shacl
  fit-map people validate ./org/people.yaml
  fit-map activity start

